	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-06-26T01:40:23">The Renewables Infrastructure Group Ltd is a United Kingdom-based closed-ended investment company, investing in and managing a portfolio of investments in renewable energy infrastructure project companies. The Company, through its subsidiary, The Renewables Infrastructure Group (UK) Limited, invests in operational renewable energy generation projects, predominantly in onshore wind and solar PV segments, across the United Kingdom and Northern Europe. The Company has a portfolio of approximately 29 investment interests in onshore wind farms and solar PV park assets located in the United Kingdom, Ireland and France. The Company's total portfolio generating capacity is approximately 439 megawatts (MW). The Company's Initial Portfolio consists of around 18 distinct wholly owned assets in the UK, France and the Republic of Ireland. 14 of the assets are operating onshore wind projects and four of the assets are operating solar PV projects.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-08-27T12:52:30">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Renewables Infrastructure Group Ltd revenues increased 13% to L12.6M. Net income increased 40% to L15.1M. Revenues reflect Interest Income increase of 34% to L11.5M. Net income benefited from Realised gain on settlement of FX forwar increase from L0K to L1.6M (income), Fair value movement of FX forward contra increase from L0K to L1.3M (income).</Text>
	</TextInfo>
